This paper presents a strategy for a robot to clean a contaminated cellular environment, which involves decision-making and movement. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the system's dynamics and control, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a mathematical analysis of the problem, which could place it in the Mathematics of Computation (cs.MA) sub-category.
